{
  "local_port": 54736,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I register my mobile number with UAN?",
  "response": "Registering your mobile number with your UAN (Universal Account Number) involves a few steps. The UAN is a unique identifier for employees in India for EPFO (Employees' Provident Fund Organisation). Here\u2019s how you can register your mobile number with UAN:\n\n1. **Visit the EPFO Website**:\n   Go to the official EPFO website (https://www.epfindia.gov.in).\n\n2. **Login to the UAN Member Portal**:\n   Click on 'For Employees' under 'Our Services'. Then, click on 'Member UAN/Online Service (OCS/OTCP)'.\n\n3. **Activate UAN**:\n   If your UAN is not activated, click on 'Activate UAN'. Enter your UAN, Member ID, Aadhaar, PAN, and your mobile number, then click 'Get Authorization Pin'. You will receive the PIN on your mobile which you can use to activate UAN by following the instructions.\n\n4. **Login**:\n   Once your UAN is activated, log in using your UAN and password.\n\n5. **Update Mobile Number**:\n   After logging in, go to the 'Manage' tab and click on 'Contact Details'. Select the 'Change Mobile Number' option.\n\n6. **Enter New Mobile Number**:\n   Enter your new mobile number and click on 'Get Authorization Pin'. You will receive a PIN on your new mobile number.\n\n7. **Confirm**:\n   Enter the PIN received on your new mobile number and click on 'Submit'. Your new mobile number will be updated in the UAN system.\n\nDuring this process, ensure you have your UAN, provident fund details, and personal information like Aadhaar or PAN handy. If you encounter any issues or need help with the process, contacting your employer or the EPFO office can be helpful.",
